  <div class="post-container">
    <h2>Post One: Why Foreign Policy Matters</h2>
    <p><em>Published: September 16, 2025</em></p>
    <p>
      Foreign policy is not just about distant diplomats negotiating treaties—
      it affects everyday people in profound ways. From trade deals that shape
      what we buy at the store, to military alliances that influence national
      security, foreign policy has a direct link to our lives.
    </p>
    <p>
      In this post, I’ll introduce why studying foreign policy is important,
      especially for students. Understanding how countries interact helps us
      see connections between global issues—like climate change, technology,
      and human rights—and the decisions our leaders make.
    </p>
    <p>
      Going forward, my blog will break down complex foreign policy topics into
      approachable posts, showing not only what is happening but also why it
      matters. The goal is to create a space where classmates, professors, and
      anyone interested can reflect on how foreign policy shapes the world we
      live in.
    </p>

